CatDescriptText: Mr. Leroy L. Jackson, bank messenger, 1323 N. Lang Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you believe churches of any denomination receive appreciation financial help from racketeers?" answer reads: "I'm most certain that they do.  It is a large amount, because even the small racketeers, whom I know are church goers, contribute money which helps to lighten the burden."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Leroy L. Jackson, wearing uniform hat with plastic rain cover, dark necktie, and rain coat with shield embellishment, standing in front of store with stack of towels and sign reading "Call Us For Home Estimates EXpress 1-3... "
